grammer
niyotte Depending on  による
～うちに 

～間に ～うち(は)

phase
Ikura desu ka いくらですか？)  How much is it?
Mou sukoshi yasuku dekimasu ka もう少し安くできますか Can you make it a little cheaper?
Sore wa chotto takai desu ne” それはちょっと高いですね That’s a bit expensive.
“Ikura desu ka?” (いくらですか？), which translates to “How much is it?”
“Shatsu no kakaku wa ikura desu ka?” (シャツの価格はいくらですか？). This translates to “What is the price of the shirt?”
 “Ringoi no kakaku wa ikura desu ka?” (りんご１キログラムの価格はいくらですか？), which means “What is the price of one kilogram of apples?”
